"Defila C., Clot B.","Phytophenological trends in Switzerland",2001,"International Journal of Biometeorology","45","4",,"203","207",,,10.1007/s004840100101,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-0035514671&partnerID=40&md5=b2f1d3c1176a4f21ebae56d5f5c7de70","MeteoSchweiz, Krähbühlstrasse 58, CH - 8044 Zürich, Switzerland","Defila, C., MeteoSchweiz, Krähbühlstrasse 58, CH - 8044 Zürich, Switzerland; Clot, B., MeteoSchweiz, Krähbühlstrasse 58, CH - 8044 Zürich, Switzerland","Nation-wide phonological observations have been made in Switzerland since 1951. In addition to these observation programmes, there are two very long phenological series in Switzerland: leaf bud burst of horse-chestnut trees has been observed in Geneva since 1808 and full flowering of cherry trees in Liestal since 1894. In addition to the presentation of these two long phenological series, trends for 896 phenological time series have been calculated with national data from 1951 to 1998. The earlier bud burst of horse-chestnut trees in Geneva can be attributed mainly to the city effect (warmth island). This phenomenon was not observed with the cherry tree flowering in Liestal. A clear trend towards earlier appearance dates in spring and a weak tendency towards later appearance dates in autumn could be shown with data from the national observation network. It must be noted that different phenophases and plant species react differently to various environmental influences.","Global climate change; Phytophenology; Switzerland; Time series; Trends","acclimatization; article; climate; environmental monitoring; growth, development and aging; plant; season; Switzerland; temperature; Acclimatization; Climate; Environmental Monitoring; Plants; Seasons; Switzerland; Temperature",,,,,,"Bider, M., Meyer, A., Lässt sich der zeitpunkt der kirschenernte der nordwestschweiz vorausbestimmen? (1946) Schweiz Z Obst Weinbau, 55, pp. 476-483; Defila, C., Pflanzenphänologie der Schweiz (1991) Veröff Schweiz Meteorol Anst, 50, pp. 1-235. , Dissertation University of Zürich; Defila, C., 45 years phytophenological observations in Switzerland, 1991 - 1995 (1996) Biometeorology, 14, pp. 175-183. , Proceedings of the 14th International Congress of Biometeorology, 1 - 8 September 1996, Ljubljana, Slovenia; Hartmann, P., (1991) Untersuchungen der Beziehungen Zwischen Witterung und der Pflanzenphänologie, pp. 1-98. , Bericht Sanasilva-Projekt; Jeanneret, F., Phänologie in einem querschnitt durch Jura, mittelland und alpen (1996) Jahrb Gg Ges BE, 59, pp. 159-203; Menzel, A., Phänologie von waldbäumen unter sich ändernden klimabedingungen - Auswertungen der beobachtungen in den in gärten und möglichkeiten der modellierung von phänodaten (1997) Forstl Forschungsber München, 186, pp. 1-147; Menzel, A., Fabian, P., Growing season extended in Europe (1999) Nature, 397, p. 659; Pfister, C., (1984) Klimageschichte der Schweiz 1525 bis 1860 - Das Klima der Schweiz 1525 bis 1860 und Seine Bedeutung in der Geschichte von Bevölkerung und Landwirtschaft, 1, pp. 1-184. , Haupt, Bern; Primault, B., Cinq ans d'observations phénologiques systématiques en Suisse (1955) Ann Schweiz Meteorol Anst, 92 JHG, pp. 74-75; Primault, B., Phänologie: Blatt 13.1, 13.2 (1984) Klimaatlas der Schweiz, 2, p. 2. , Kirchhofer W (ed) Lieferung. Verlag des Bundesamtes für Landestopographie, Bern; Schnelle, F., Pflanzenphänologie (1955) Probleme der Bioklimatologie, 3, pp. 1-299. , Akakdemische Verlagsgesellschaft, Leipzig; Schreiber, K.F., (1977) Wärmegliederung der Schweiz. Grundlagen für die Raumplanung, pp. 1-69. , Eidg Justiz Polizeidepartement, Bern; Vassella, A., Phänologie von waldbäumen (1997) Buwal Umwelt-materialien, 73, pp. 9-75","Defila, C.; MeteoSchweiz, Krähbühlstrasse 58, CH - 8044 Zürich, Switzerland; email: claudio.defila@meteoschweiz.ch",,,,,,,,00207128,,IJBMA,11769321,"English","Int. J. Biometeorol.",Article,Scopus,2-s2.0-0035514671
